        i.
            Plasma components means the substances that make up blood plasma.
        ii.
            54 * (1 - .44) = 30.24g
        iii.
            Glucose is reabsorbed in the nephron so it can be later respired to release energy to sustain bodily functions, so that energy and food, which may be difficult to come by in the wild, is not wasted (wasted by being excreted without being respired, so energy is not released).
        iv.
            The high protein and salt content will cause blood concentration to increase. This will be detected by the hypothalamus, which will send a nervous signal to the pituitary gland, causing it to increase secretion of ADH. This increases the permeability of the collecting duct, so more water is reabsorbed via osmosis, so less water will be excreted in the form of urine, so therefore less but more concentrated urine will be produced. Further, the mass of sodium filtered and mass excreted will increase, while percentage reabsorbed will decreased. This is because the kidney will seek to control the body's salt content, so an increase in intake of salt and hence sodium will cause more to be excreted and hence less to be reabsorbed to facilitate this. This will also mean there is more sodium in the urine of the person. However, there will not be more protein in the urine of the person. This is because protein is too large to pass through the glomerulus, basement membrane, and capillary wall, so protein passes out of the kidneys via the renal vein and will not enter the urine.
